1
00:00:50,954 --> 00:00:52,997
No! No!

2
00:00:55,006 --> 00:00:56,006
No.

3
00:00:56,431 --> 00:00:59,184
Rhea! Rhea! Rhea!

4
00:00:59,746 --> 00:01:01,081
I have a student.

5
00:01:01,662 --> 00:01:02,746
Stein Alberts.

6
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:04,647
Third year, B.S. Math.

7
00:01:04,965 --> 00:01:06,258
Actually, he’s really good.

8
00:01:06,936 --> 00:01:08,536
So, you're always in front of the stage,

9
00:01:08,957 --> 00:01:10,250
watching the production

10
00:01:10,715 --> 00:01:12,092
from the audience's point of view.

11
00:01:13,215 --> 00:01:14,215
Right?

12
00:01:14,539 --> 00:01:16,416
I am Moriarty.

13
00:01:22,402 --> 00:01:23,528
How did you know we're here?

14
00:01:27,058 --> 00:01:28,852
What kind of question is that, Loki?

15
00:01:29,752 --> 00:01:31,420
As far as I remember,

16
00:01:32,219 --> 00:01:34,513
didn’t someone die because you meddled?

17
00:01:34,812 --> 00:01:37,642
Loki, please, save me.

18
00:01:42,904 --> 00:01:43,904
Stein!

19
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:46,063
One more thing...

20
00:02:04,159 --> 00:02:05,952
Is this the Q.E.D. Club?

21
00:02:06,583 --> 00:02:08,710
I want you to join the Q.E.D. Club.

22
00:02:27,923 --> 00:02:30,384
The Q.E.D. Club

23
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:34,237
is the one and only detective club
here in Clark University.

24
00:02:34,755 --> 00:02:36,256
I hope it’s always like this.

25
00:02:37,977 --> 00:02:41,606
We can prevent the tragedy
before it happens.

26
00:02:41,950 --> 00:02:44,661
We can save even more lives.

27
00:02:56,988 --> 00:02:58,198
I knew you would be here.

28
00:03:00,599 --> 00:03:01,599
Luthor?

29
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,725
What are you doing here?

30
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:08,479
Well, I'm obviously here
to check on my brother.

31
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:10,648
How’s he holding up?

32
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:14,194
As you can see, he's not here.

33
00:03:16,715 --> 00:03:18,298
Well, that’s obvious,

34
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,320
but you should be able to tell me that.

35
00:03:20,885 --> 00:03:22,093
I'm well aware, Lorelei,

36
00:03:22,118 --> 00:03:24,296
that the two of you live together
in an apartment

37
00:03:24,321 --> 00:03:25,817
three blocks away from here.

38
00:03:26,434 --> 00:03:28,144
Isn’t that right, Miss Lorelei?

39
00:03:30,946 --> 00:03:34,199
Why don't you just visit him
if you're really that concerned about him?

40
00:03:35,474 --> 00:03:36,474
I could.

41
00:03:37,487 --> 00:03:38,530
But, you know…

42
00:03:39,278 --> 00:03:40,737
I don’t wish to ruin his day.

43
00:03:40,894 --> 00:03:43,313
It seems like the mere sight
of my shadow is...

44
00:03:44,491 --> 00:03:46,034
is enough to upset him,

45
00:03:46,231 --> 00:03:47,440
to send him bollocks.

46
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:52,357
What more if I checked on him in person?

47
00:03:55,232 --> 00:03:56,232
Fair enough.

48
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:03,020
It also seems like he’s enjoying himself
with the suspension and all.

49
00:04:03,635 --> 00:04:05,387
He hates going to class, so...

50
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:09,040
he’s probably grateful
that this is his punishment.

51
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:12,584
By the way,

52
00:04:13,419 --> 00:04:14,796
how’s the progress...

53
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:17,130
of the campus police

54
00:04:17,131 --> 00:04:19,467
and the school admin's investigation
on Stein?

55
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:22,971
On the allegation
that our school’s math prodigy

56
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:25,890
is a criminal mastermind?

57
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:29,851
Listen, I’m not really supposed
to share this

58
00:04:30,016 --> 00:04:32,185
since the investigation
is still ongoing...

59
00:04:32,829 --> 00:04:33,829
but…

60
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,776
I guess it’s best that you are informed.

61
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:42,906
At the moment,
there's not a single shred of evidence

62
00:04:42,907 --> 00:04:45,493
that he is what my brother
claims him to be.

63
00:04:46,202 --> 00:04:47,328
No evidence?

64
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:50,999
Did the campus police check his phone?

65
00:04:51,874 --> 00:04:55,377
There might be conversations
or transactions there linking him

66
00:04:55,378 --> 00:04:58,131
to the cases happening here at Clark U.

67
00:04:58,548 --> 00:05:02,176
Unfortunately, there’s nothing
in his phone that will incriminate him.

68
00:05:03,106 --> 00:05:04,316
No texts,

69
00:05:04,743 --> 00:05:05,744
no calls,

70
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:09,160
beside one made by my brother but...

71
00:05:09,185 --> 00:05:10,559
the school’s investigation shows

72
00:05:10,584 --> 00:05:13,912
that Stein was actually Moriarty’s victim.

73
00:05:13,945 --> 00:05:16,489
He was locked
in an abandoned building apparently,

74
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:20,170
so, he couldn’t join
the math screening competition.

75
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:22,655
So, I was thinking,

76
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:26,826
how could he be the mastermind
if he himself was a victim?

77
00:05:27,201 --> 00:05:29,537
Luthor, of course,
that’s what he wants you to think.

78
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:32,498
That he’s the victim,
but he planned all of this.

79
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:35,710
He’s trying to trick you all,
so you won’t suspect him!

80
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:39,297
That’s what you like to think.

81
00:05:39,422 --> 00:05:42,175
That’s what you and Loki want to think.

82
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:45,345
Even if it’s not true,
even if he is not Moriarty.

83
00:05:45,618 --> 00:05:48,264
No, Luthor. Stein admitted he’s Moriarty.

84
00:05:48,454 --> 00:05:49,782
It came straight from his own mouth!

85
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:50,807
Oh, yeah?

86
00:05:52,340 --> 00:05:55,092
Where’s the evidence? Did you record it?

87
00:05:55,917 --> 00:06:00,672
Did he just casually pick up
a piece of paper and sign it?

88
00:06:02,226 --> 00:06:05,145
Lorelei, I didn’t come here
just to check on my brother.

89
00:06:06,274 --> 00:06:08,813
The student council
is deciding this Friday

90
00:06:08,838 --> 00:06:11,007
whether this club
should be dissolve or not.

91
00:06:11,704 --> 00:06:12,681
What?

92
00:06:12,706 --> 00:06:14,165
To be perfectly candid,

93
00:06:14,390 --> 00:06:16,267
we’re not exactly on your favor.

94
00:06:16,526 --> 00:06:17,777
What motion is that?

95
00:06:18,228 --> 00:06:19,882
Why is our club suddenly involved?

96
00:06:19,907 --> 00:06:21,797
This issue is between Loki and Stein!

97
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:26,051
The admin has reasons to believe
that this club is enabling my brother

98
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:28,536
to pursue wrong leads
and fanciful theories

99
00:06:28,561 --> 00:06:30,438
that may harm one of our prodigies.

100
00:06:31,032 --> 00:06:36,007
The school administration has left us
to decide if you guys stay or not.

101
00:06:36,032 --> 00:06:38,556
You didn’t even do anything
to defend your brother

102
00:06:38,581 --> 00:06:41,084
and the club that means so much to him!

103
00:06:41,292 --> 00:06:44,253
If you think I didn’t do anything
for my brother,

104
00:06:44,458 --> 00:06:46,419
and you think
I didn’t pull strings for him,

105
00:06:47,093 --> 00:06:48,845
he would be in jail a long time ago.

106
00:06:50,665 --> 00:06:53,081
I cannot fix all of his messes.

107
00:06:54,497 --> 00:06:56,082
Please send my regards to him.

108
00:06:58,455 --> 00:07:00,040
Now, if you’ll excuse me.

109
00:07:12,585 --> 00:07:14,086
This can’t be happening.

110
00:07:16,695 --> 00:07:18,377
♪ Shadows. ♪

111
00:07:19,589 --> 00:07:22,258
♪ In the dark are crawling. ♪

112
00:07:22,709 --> 00:07:26,941
♪ Keeping watch and barring your way. ♪

113
00:07:26,966 --> 00:07:30,511
♪ As if the line could not be crossed. ♪

114
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:34,870
♪ To every scream and every tremor. ♪

115
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:38,039
♪ These walls remain the only witness. ♪

116
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:41,001
♪ Every noise is etched in here. ♪

117
00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:45,506
♪ Like fire and ammunition
for your memory. ♪

118
00:07:46,953 --> 00:07:49,080
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

119
00:07:50,261 --> 00:07:52,638
♪ The threats poised to strike. ♪

120
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:57,393
♪ For this world ♪

121
00:07:58,060 --> 00:08:00,687
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

122
00:08:00,688 --> 00:08:03,149
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

123
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:06,277
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

124
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:11,115
♪ For this world ♪

125
00:08:11,824 --> 00:08:14,367
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

126
00:08:14,368 --> 00:08:19,207
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

127
00:08:26,085 --> 00:08:28,671
Loki! What have you done
with my teddy bear?

128
00:08:29,583 --> 00:08:30,583
Correction!

129
00:08:31,453 --> 00:08:32,454
My teddy bear.

130
00:08:33,207 --> 00:08:34,542
No longer yours.

131
00:08:35,026 --> 00:08:37,569
Have you forgotten that you
transferred its ownership to me

132
00:08:37,594 --> 00:08:39,054
after throwing it away?

133
00:08:39,564 --> 00:08:40,536
That’s not the issue here!

134
00:08:40,561 --> 00:08:42,385
Why do you have to hang him?

135
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,763
Hey! Don’t worry.

136
00:08:47,127 --> 00:08:48,127
Don’t worry.

137
00:08:50,276 --> 00:08:51,444
Theodore doesn’t mind.

138
00:08:52,685 --> 00:08:54,478
You should even be proud of him.

139
00:08:55,814 --> 00:08:58,611
He helped me prove
the innocence of a young man

140
00:08:59,201 --> 00:09:01,119
accused of hanging his girlfriend.

141
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:06,088
He couldn’t have committed the crime
because his height lacks a few inches.

142
00:09:07,639 --> 00:09:10,934
The culprit is someone
who is taller than him,

143
00:09:11,829 --> 00:09:14,790
around 6'3".

144
00:09:15,396 --> 00:09:16,355
Theodore?

145
00:09:16,380 --> 00:09:18,256
Why does his name sound so old?

146
00:09:19,975 --> 00:09:21,435
Teddy bears were named

147
00:09:22,135 --> 00:09:24,789
after US President Theodore Roosevelt.

148
00:09:25,049 --> 00:09:26,248
Yes, I know!

149
00:09:26,273 --> 00:09:28,692
But there are so many names
to choose from.

150
00:09:37,708 --> 00:09:39,974
By the way, Professor Morayta
was asking how you're doing.

151
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:44,542
Luthor also visited.

152
00:09:46,253 --> 00:09:48,013
He was asking
how you're doing as well, Loki.

153
00:09:50,914 --> 00:09:56,378
And he also has a new update
regarding the Moriarty case.

154
00:09:57,382 --> 00:10:02,554
He said that there's still
no concrete evidence against Stein.

155
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:06,188
Even after checking his phone,
they found nothing.

156
00:10:07,901 --> 00:10:09,486
And lastly...

157
00:10:11,052 --> 00:10:13,054
he also mentioned to me that...

158
00:10:13,957 --> 00:10:17,293
the student council is planning
to dissolve the Q.E.D. Club.

159
00:10:23,515 --> 00:10:25,559
Aren’t you going to say anything, Loki?

160
00:10:26,387 --> 00:10:28,097
I’ve already given you so many updates.

161
00:10:29,307 --> 00:10:30,974
Moriarty is an able strategist.

162
00:10:32,140 --> 00:10:33,392
The fake abduction...

163
00:10:35,024 --> 00:10:37,401
his phone showing nothing illegal.

164
00:10:38,487 --> 00:10:40,531
Every piece was positioned perfectly

165
00:10:40,790 --> 00:10:44,377
to ensure that not a single crime
would be traced back to him.

166
00:10:45,973 --> 00:10:48,767
We need to secure
an irrefutable piece of evidence,

167
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:51,025
if we want to bring him back to justice.

168
00:10:52,483 --> 00:10:54,319
So what happens to the Q.E.D. Club?

169
00:10:54,943 --> 00:10:59,155
Why do you seem like you’re not worried
that they might dissolve this?

170
00:11:00,957 --> 00:11:02,388
I’m suspended, Lorelei.

171
00:11:03,401 --> 00:11:05,487
So I can’t do anything
for the club right now.

172
00:11:06,545 --> 00:11:08,588
If the president is unavailable…

173
00:11:09,806 --> 00:11:11,975
the burden to deal with alarming issues

174
00:11:12,345 --> 00:11:13,763
falls to the vice president.

175
00:11:15,147 --> 00:11:16,315
Which happens to be you.

176
00:11:17,181 --> 00:11:18,724
So that’s it? Just like that?

177
00:11:19,673 --> 00:11:21,049
Isn’t the club dear to you?

178
00:11:21,974 --> 00:11:25,473
Don’t you feel even a little regret
that you might lose a place

179
00:11:25,506 --> 00:11:27,675
where you made so many memories?

180
00:11:29,340 --> 00:11:32,593
The club might just be a small room
to most students in Clark U…

181
00:11:33,718 --> 00:11:35,261
but not to you, Loki.

182
00:11:36,559 --> 00:11:39,270
For you it can be more than just a room.

183
00:11:41,446 --> 00:11:43,198
What about your memories with Rhe...

184
00:11:48,542 --> 00:11:50,462
It looks like you still want
to ask me something.

185
00:11:50,727 --> 00:11:51,727
Go ahead.

186
00:11:53,045 --> 00:11:54,838
I’m in a mood to give you answers.

187
00:11:58,524 --> 00:12:00,109
Do you feel good now?

188
00:12:02,213 --> 00:12:05,675
Have you finally released all the anger
you’ve been keeping toward Moriarty?

189
00:12:08,242 --> 00:12:09,368
Strangely...

190
00:12:10,105 --> 00:12:11,982
the feeling’s far from satisfaction.

191
00:12:13,510 --> 00:12:15,304
I should be happy that I got my revenge.

192
00:12:17,087 --> 00:12:18,087
But I’m not.

193
00:12:20,329 --> 00:12:21,872
I feel underwhelmed.

194
00:12:24,028 --> 00:12:25,488
I feel disappointed.

195
00:12:27,803 --> 00:12:28,803
Well...

196
00:12:29,555 --> 00:12:32,391
maybe that’s not what justice
is supposed to feel like.

197
00:12:35,207 --> 00:12:36,207
Lori.

198
00:12:39,098 --> 00:12:41,392
Lori! Lori! What the heck?

199
00:12:41,736 --> 00:12:43,404
Oh, my bangs! What is that?

200
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:47,604
Why are you messing
with this harmless teddy bear?

201
00:12:48,138 --> 00:12:49,346
Sorry, Tita.

202
00:12:49,371 --> 00:12:53,000
It’s just that Loki messed
with my teddy bear!

203
00:12:53,642 --> 00:12:54,642
Correction.

204
00:12:55,485 --> 00:12:56,611
My teddy bear.

205
00:12:57,169 --> 00:12:58,377
Whoever’s teddy bear this is,

206
00:12:58,402 --> 00:13:00,111
your teddy bear, her teddy bear,
whoever’s teddy bear it is,

207
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:01,529
can you please put
that teddy bear down already?

208
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:03,693
I feel bad, and I’m hurt!

209
00:13:07,291 --> 00:13:08,417
What the heck?

210
00:13:09,724 --> 00:13:12,183
Tita, it looks like you’re busy right now.

211
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:13,333
Yeah, I’m really busy!

212
00:13:13,334 --> 00:13:16,279
But it looks like you’re even busier
finding time to do that!

213
00:13:17,029 --> 00:13:19,690
I’m busy because I need
to have this ceiling fixed.

214
00:13:19,896 --> 00:13:22,884
I was going to give some snacks
to the workers,

215
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,294
and I included you as well.

216
00:13:24,319 --> 00:13:26,405
So, there, have some snacks.

217
00:13:26,630 --> 00:13:29,307
This teddy bear must
be getting hot. Poor thing.

218
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:30,851
It’s been there for so long, right?

219
00:13:31,182 --> 00:13:32,182
Huh?

220
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:35,740
By the way, Lorelei,

221
00:13:36,127 --> 00:13:40,423
do you have anything to do
tomorrow after your class?

222
00:13:41,310 --> 00:13:43,631
I think I’m still free tomorrow
after class, Tita.

223
00:13:43,937 --> 00:13:46,022
Why? Do you need something from me?

224
00:13:47,380 --> 00:13:49,118
Nothing. Just asking.

225
00:13:49,177 --> 00:13:51,481
You know me. I like asking questions.

226
00:13:51,506 --> 00:13:52,506
How are you?

227
00:13:53,005 --> 00:13:53,832
I’m fine now.

228
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,291
See? I really like asking questions.

229
00:13:55,292 --> 00:13:57,545
I’ll go ahead. Make sure you eat, okay?

230
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:18,857
Get well soon, Stein.

231
00:14:20,416 --> 00:14:24,921
I hope you wake up from your coma, Stein,
so you can tell the whole truth.

232
00:14:25,945 --> 00:14:27,321
Justice for Stein!

233
00:14:27,795 --> 00:14:29,589
We can't let this slide.

234
00:14:31,132 --> 00:14:33,760
Sending prayers, Stein. Get well soon.

235
00:14:45,045 --> 00:14:46,088
Oh, right.

236
00:14:59,199 --> 00:15:02,232
If only they truly knew
who the real Stein is.

237
00:15:05,065 --> 00:15:06,358
Loki was right.

238
00:15:06,904 --> 00:15:08,948
You’re a really good strategist.

239
00:15:09,583 --> 00:15:13,336
Is this part of your game
to make Loki look like the bad guy?

240
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:18,464
You’ve killed so many fellow students.

241
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:21,629
If Loki doesn't care
whether you live or die,

242
00:15:22,289 --> 00:15:23,289
I do.

243
00:15:23,648 --> 00:15:25,400
I want you to stay alive

244
00:15:25,828 --> 00:15:27,704
so you can pay for what you did.

245
00:15:32,896 --> 00:15:34,033
The Q.E.D. Club will make sure

246
00:15:34,058 --> 00:15:36,727
you can’t escape
the sins you’ve committed.

247
00:15:37,491 --> 00:15:38,810
Remember that, Stein.

248
00:15:48,791 --> 00:15:50,460
Pawn to E6.

249
00:15:53,619 --> 00:15:55,287
Queen to E7.

250
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:58,498
Checkmate.

251
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:01,830
Why are you up so early?

252
00:16:14,309 --> 00:16:15,560
I want you to have this.

253
00:16:16,914 --> 00:16:18,354
What am I supposed to do about that?

254
00:16:18,496 --> 00:16:20,123
I have my own laptop anyway.

255
00:16:22,379 --> 00:16:24,740
Yesterday, you seemed
really concerned about our club.

256
00:16:25,563 --> 00:16:30,777
Thus, I’m offering you its salvation.

257
00:16:36,247 --> 00:16:38,263
Do you want me to smash this
in your brother’s face

258
00:16:38,288 --> 00:16:40,624
and the rest of the student council?

259
00:16:42,175 --> 00:16:43,218
Sure.

260
00:16:44,742 --> 00:16:46,619
That’s fun. But just him.

261
00:16:47,568 --> 00:16:48,777
Spare the others.

262
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:55,597
Kidding aside,
this laptop is a pandora’s box.

263
00:16:56,645 --> 00:16:58,272
Once what’s inside this leaks,

264
00:16:59,126 --> 00:17:02,046
the campus will definitely be in chaos.

265
00:17:02,890 --> 00:17:05,017
But if you’re careful enough
in opening it,

266
00:17:05,666 --> 00:17:09,962
it can make anyone bow to your will.

267
00:17:10,671 --> 00:17:12,794
And if you want to save our club,

268
00:17:13,367 --> 00:17:16,119
all you have to do is log in

269
00:17:17,222 --> 00:17:18,724
and browse some files.

270
00:17:21,091 --> 00:17:22,092
Okay.

271
00:17:34,195 --> 00:17:35,363
There's a password?

272
00:17:35,769 --> 00:17:37,730
It wouldn't be fun
if I tell you right away.

273
00:17:38,359 --> 00:17:39,527
Try deducing it.

274
00:17:39,552 --> 00:17:40,720
Are you serious?

275
00:17:41,615 --> 00:17:43,576
My laptop has a nine-digit code.

276
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:49,793
When decrypted, those numbers
will reveal the word "detective."

277
00:17:50,043 --> 00:17:51,336
Sounds easy, right?

278
00:17:51,642 --> 00:17:52,894
What’s easy about that?

279
00:17:54,131 --> 00:17:58,427
Well, those who aren't aware of my methods
will have a hard time figuring it out.

280
00:17:58,669 --> 00:17:59,994
I already expected
that there was a possibility

281
00:17:59,995 --> 00:18:01,747
our club would be dissolved,

282
00:18:03,252 --> 00:18:04,754
so I prepared for it.

283
00:18:05,521 --> 00:18:08,087
And this day has finally come!

284
00:18:09,069 --> 00:18:10,862
The salvation of our club...

285
00:18:12,669 --> 00:18:14,170
is now in your hands.

286
00:18:15,216 --> 00:18:17,927
Wow. You’re really serious.

287
00:18:18,593 --> 00:18:20,261
Okay, well...

288
00:18:21,531 --> 00:18:24,826
any clue that might help me out?

289
00:18:30,621 --> 00:18:32,289
You can try…

290
00:18:33,161 --> 00:18:34,871
You can try Mary Had A Little Lamb.

291
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:53,173
Loki, you're supposed to help me,
yet you're making this harder.

292
00:18:55,342 --> 00:19:00,764
Let’s try 4, 5, 2, 5, 3,

293
00:19:01,665 --> 00:19:05,336
2, 9, 4, 5.

294
00:19:07,411 --> 00:19:08,411
What?

295
00:19:09,248 --> 00:19:11,834
So there’s a limit
for incorrect passwords?

296
00:19:11,859 --> 00:19:15,571
What’s with Loki?
He could’ve just told me.

297
00:19:26,657 --> 00:19:28,659
I can’t just keep guessing anymore.

298
00:19:32,099 --> 00:19:36,937
How would a children’s song
help me encrypt the word "detective"?

299
00:19:37,798 --> 00:19:39,008
Is this data?

300
00:19:39,861 --> 00:19:42,155
When was this composed?

301
00:19:45,058 --> 00:19:47,858
It might not be a date shift cipher.

302
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:53,025
Okay.

303
00:20:38,695 --> 00:20:39,738
Yes!

304
00:21:09,726 --> 00:21:11,853
Okay. I'm doing this for the club.

305
00:21:12,995 --> 00:21:16,040
I need to speak with the Vice President.
Is he there?

306
00:21:16,917 --> 00:21:19,753
Sorry, miss. We’re in a meeting.

307
00:21:20,021 --> 00:21:22,863
But I can relay your message
to him if you want.

308
00:21:22,864 --> 00:21:26,326
No! I need to speak with him in person.
This is an urgent matter.

309
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:29,023
But, miss, we’re in a meeting.

310
00:21:29,048 --> 00:21:30,899
You don’t understand. This is important!

311
00:21:30,924 --> 00:21:32,383
- I need to speak with him!
- But...

312
00:21:35,782 --> 00:21:37,242
Is there a problem here?

313
00:21:39,521 --> 00:21:43,858
What’s so urgent that you seek
an audience with us, Ms. Lorelei?

314
00:21:44,716 --> 00:21:47,760
I have an offer that you
and the student council can’t refuse.

315
00:22:53,084 --> 00:22:54,794
I’m Lorelei Rios.

316
00:22:55,895 --> 00:22:58,731
And I’m speaking
on behalf of the Q.E.D. Club.

317
00:22:59,505 --> 00:23:00,965
I know you, Lorelei.

318
00:23:01,510 --> 00:23:05,138
I’m Emeraude Emerson,
the Student Council President.

319
00:23:06,035 --> 00:23:08,037
How can we help you?

320
00:23:10,072 --> 00:23:14,845
I want you to make sure
our club won’t be dissolved.

321
00:23:15,648 --> 00:23:18,234
But that's not something we can control.

322
00:23:19,050 --> 00:23:23,847
We’ll vote tomorrow on whether
your club should still be retained.

323
00:23:24,345 --> 00:23:26,803
We can’t dictate each person’s choice.

324
00:23:28,350 --> 00:23:29,935
That’s why I have an offer,

325
00:23:30,846 --> 00:23:35,350
to make sure
the majority will be unanimous

326
00:23:35,608 --> 00:23:38,777
in not agreeing to dissolve our club.

327
00:23:39,310 --> 00:23:41,020
Okay. Let’s see.

328
00:23:58,632 --> 00:23:59,799
Wait a minute...

329
00:24:01,290 --> 00:24:02,576
These are...

330
00:24:02,601 --> 00:24:04,519
Do you remember Charles Meliton?

331
00:24:04,985 --> 00:24:09,280
The serial blackmailer
that tried to extort money

332
00:24:09,577 --> 00:24:12,495
from one of your fellow
student council officers

333
00:24:12,896 --> 00:24:15,648
in exchange for not leaking
those set of photos?

334
00:24:17,715 --> 00:24:20,927
If you dissolve our club tomorrow,

335
00:24:21,258 --> 00:24:25,846
you can expect those photographs
to be leaked online,

336
00:24:26,294 --> 00:24:30,089
via an anonymous user on social media.

337
00:24:30,906 --> 00:24:33,658
It’ll be a huge scandal if that happens.

338
00:24:34,432 --> 00:24:37,409
You know, Lorelei, it’s kinda funny
that you think that this

339
00:24:37,731 --> 00:24:40,525
is enough for us to bend the knee.

340
00:24:42,242 --> 00:24:44,661
I think you have mistaken us, Lorelei.

341
00:24:45,443 --> 00:24:49,322
I don’t know
if I’m the only one who noticed,

342
00:24:50,268 --> 00:24:53,425
or if you’ve been wondering too,

343
00:24:53,864 --> 00:24:57,409
but with everything
that’s been happening at Clark U...

344
00:24:58,319 --> 00:25:00,279
none of this is making it to the news?

345
00:25:01,710 --> 00:25:03,128
I wonder why.

346
00:25:04,247 --> 00:25:07,166
Maybe a media blackout, perhaps?

347
00:25:08,369 --> 00:25:10,497
In the photos you’re holding,

348
00:25:11,049 --> 00:25:12,342
as you can see,

349
00:25:12,681 --> 00:25:16,351
some Student Council officers
are involved

350
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:19,768
as well as some members
of the Executive Committee.

351
00:25:20,447 --> 00:25:22,366
And after doing some research,

352
00:25:22,807 --> 00:25:25,258
I found that they actually come

353
00:25:25,283 --> 00:25:27,901
from some pretty influential families.

354
00:25:29,684 --> 00:25:33,062
Can you imagine the damage this would do?

355
00:25:33,876 --> 00:25:37,838
To their families' honor
and to the school's image,

356
00:25:38,437 --> 00:25:42,900
if those photographs
were, say, to be leaked?

357
00:25:43,932 --> 00:25:46,059
It would be massive. You're right.

358
00:25:47,112 --> 00:25:50,427
You know, I can’t believe
that you’re using my brother’s method

359
00:25:50,452 --> 00:25:51,828
to bring us to our knee.

360
00:25:52,604 --> 00:25:55,542
You know that it all hundred percent
screams Loki.

361
00:25:59,432 --> 00:26:01,726
Very well, regarding your offer...

362
00:26:03,099 --> 00:26:05,725
we would have to make sure

363
00:26:05,750 --> 00:26:09,462
that none of the contents
will be leaked to the public.

364
00:26:11,568 --> 00:26:12,903
Can you keep your word?

365
00:26:13,816 --> 00:26:15,443
You have my word, Luthor.

366
00:26:16,138 --> 00:26:17,723
And my word is my bond.

367
00:26:18,201 --> 00:26:19,744
Yeah. You better make sure.

368
00:26:20,891 --> 00:26:23,435
So, do we have a deal?

369
00:26:56,484 --> 00:26:57,860
I just did that!

370
00:26:58,366 --> 00:26:59,366
Okay.

371
00:27:10,234 --> 00:27:11,277
Hello, Loki!

372
00:27:12,263 --> 00:27:14,640
Yeah. Any updates?

373
00:27:15,758 --> 00:27:16,801
They took the bait!

374
00:27:17,687 --> 00:27:19,272
They took my offer.

375
00:27:19,297 --> 00:27:20,554
We made a deal.

376
00:27:20,883 --> 00:27:23,219
They won’t dissolve
the Q.E.D. Club anymore.

377
00:27:24,994 --> 00:27:25,994
Okay.

378
00:27:26,818 --> 00:27:27,818
Huh?

379
00:27:28,622 --> 00:27:29,623
Just okay?

380
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:31,816
No “good job” or anything?

381
00:27:32,281 --> 00:27:36,201
I was 99.9% certain
they’d accept our offer.

382
00:27:37,388 --> 00:27:38,639
Okay. Fine.

383
00:27:40,796 --> 00:27:42,130
Wait, Lorelei.

384
00:27:45,267 --> 00:27:46,643
Are you free this weekend?

385
00:27:48,123 --> 00:27:50,667
I don’t have anything planned
this weekend yet.

386
00:27:51,049 --> 00:27:52,049
Why?

387
00:27:54,865 --> 00:27:56,533
I’d like to invite you on a date.

388
00:27:56,879 --> 00:27:58,923
Huh? What?

389
00:28:02,985 --> 00:28:05,570
I said, I’d like to invite you on a date.

390
00:28:07,099 --> 00:28:09,476
Come on, Loki. Is this a prank?

391
00:28:10,927 --> 00:28:11,927
Yup!

392
00:28:13,686 --> 00:28:14,686
Okay.

393
00:28:15,818 --> 00:28:18,612
But, seriously, are you really free
this weekend?

394
00:28:19,227 --> 00:28:21,771
An acquaintance needs our help
with a strange case.

395
00:28:22,242 --> 00:28:25,203
And we both owe him a favor,
so he deserves our help.

396
00:28:25,745 --> 00:28:29,196
Wait, in what way do I owe this person?

397
00:28:29,724 --> 00:28:32,185
And I don’t even know
that acquaintance of yours.

398
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:33,460
Just do it!

399
00:28:33,954 --> 00:28:35,497
You’ll find out this weekend.

400
00:28:36,147 --> 00:28:37,857
Just make sure you’re free this Saturday.

401
00:28:38,116 --> 00:28:39,116
But...

402
00:28:55,191 --> 00:28:56,317
You seem happy.

403
00:28:58,929 --> 00:29:00,180
What do you need, Maggie?

404
00:29:01,760 --> 00:29:02,760
Nothing.

405
00:29:03,241 --> 00:29:06,870
I just heard you made a deal
with the Student Council.

406
00:29:07,162 --> 00:29:10,415
They say you have
some very scandalous files?

407
00:29:13,670 --> 00:29:14,963
Impressive.

408
00:29:16,540 --> 00:29:18,125
Your blackmail is effective.

409
00:29:18,887 --> 00:29:21,556
Though I’m a bit disappointed because

410
00:29:22,189 --> 00:29:25,108
you’re starting to pick up Loki’s schemes.

411
00:29:25,517 --> 00:29:27,311
I expected more from you.

412
00:29:27,506 --> 00:29:31,218
Sorry, but I don’t care
if you’re disappointed in me.

413
00:29:31,524 --> 00:29:33,568
I don’t need to please you.

414
00:29:34,553 --> 00:29:39,058
I still don’t get why you’re still
so invested in the Q.E.D. Club.

415
00:29:39,710 --> 00:29:44,882
Don’t you want a quiet life
and just finish your degree in peace?

416
00:29:45,950 --> 00:29:49,871
And what? Just turn a blind eye
to my dying schoolmates?

417
00:29:50,329 --> 00:29:52,165
I can’t do that, Maggie.

418
00:29:52,597 --> 00:29:56,809
But, yes, you’re right.
I do want a quiet life.

419
00:29:57,485 --> 00:30:00,946
But we can only study in peace,
if we’re safe.

420
00:30:01,307 --> 00:30:03,601
And that’s why I’m with the Q.E.D. Club!

421
00:30:08,115 --> 00:30:09,117
Excuse me.

422
00:30:24,423 --> 00:30:26,091
Hello, Tita Martha?

423
00:30:27,066 --> 00:30:28,401
Hello, Lori!

424
00:30:28,426 --> 00:30:30,261
I know you’re still in class,

425
00:30:30,395 --> 00:30:35,183
I was wondering if you could meet me
at the coffee shop.

426
00:30:35,468 --> 00:30:39,044
It’s next to your school,
Diogenes Coffee Shop.

427
00:30:39,310 --> 00:30:40,520
After your class.

428
00:30:42,340 --> 00:30:43,550
Okay, Tita.

429
00:30:43,775 --> 00:30:45,819
Ah, okay. Let's meet, okay?

430
00:30:46,124 --> 00:30:47,792
Okay. See you there.

431
00:31:08,092 --> 00:31:09,134
Lori.

432
00:31:11,956 --> 00:31:15,042
Tita, what does this mean?

433
00:31:17,142 --> 00:31:18,310
Because...

434
00:31:22,272 --> 00:31:25,192
Come on. Come on. Come on!

435
00:31:28,678 --> 00:31:29,762
Come here. Come here!

436
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:37,604
Papa?

437
00:31:38,446 --> 00:31:40,239
What are you doing here?

438
00:31:45,940 --> 00:31:47,358
I’m here to pick you up.

439
00:31:48,418 --> 00:31:49,503
You’re going home.

440
00:31:50,312 --> 00:31:51,450
Wait. Wait!

441
00:31:51,685 --> 00:31:53,228
Sit down. Sit down first.

442
00:31:54,093 --> 00:31:55,178
Wait.

443
00:31:56,486 --> 00:32:00,490
Kuya, don’t be so abrupt with Lori.

444
00:32:01,311 --> 00:32:04,940
Maybe you can talk
things through properly.

445
00:32:05,959 --> 00:32:07,585
Thank you, Martha.

446
00:32:18,188 --> 00:32:19,231
Alright.

447
00:32:32,533 --> 00:32:34,786
We haven’t seen each other for months,

448
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:39,165
and now you suddenly show up
just to send me home?

449
00:32:42,180 --> 00:32:43,347
That’s so...

450
00:32:43,372 --> 00:32:45,082
Tea? Coffee?

451
00:32:45,553 --> 00:32:46,554
Neither.

452
00:32:47,696 --> 00:32:49,240
All I want to know...

453
00:32:50,009 --> 00:32:53,554
is why you’re making me go home
in the middle of the school year.

454
00:32:55,189 --> 00:32:57,942
This is not the first time
you get yourself into trouble.

455
00:32:58,900 --> 00:33:03,029
I thought sending you to your aunt
would straighten you out.

456
00:33:04,447 --> 00:33:06,449
Clearly, I was mistaken.

457
00:33:18,204 --> 00:33:19,204
Loki!

458
00:33:19,455 --> 00:33:22,082
- Stop it! Stop it!
- Fucking bastard!

459
00:33:22,083 --> 00:33:24,084
That's enough! That's enough!

460
00:33:24,085 --> 00:33:25,421
Where did you get this?

461
00:33:26,869 --> 00:33:28,328
That’s not important anymore.

462
00:33:29,556 --> 00:33:36,272
Lori, you’re befriending
violent people like that.

463
00:33:38,088 --> 00:33:39,798
Why are you hanging out with them?

464
00:33:41,369 --> 00:33:43,037
Have you become like that too? Huh?

465
00:33:43,945 --> 00:33:45,863
I’m so disappointed in you.

466
00:33:47,201 --> 00:33:51,497
Anyway, I’m here
to take you back to Manila.

467
00:33:52,291 --> 00:33:56,337
You’ll be studying again
at St. Bartholomew.

468
00:33:57,504 --> 00:34:00,382
- I don’t want to go back there.
- You have nothing to worry about.

469
00:34:01,189 --> 00:34:05,068
Everyone involved in that incident
has been expelled.

470
00:34:09,756 --> 00:34:11,468
Didn’t Al tell you?

471
00:34:13,235 --> 00:34:16,446
Anyway, I know
the board of directors there.

472
00:34:17,666 --> 00:34:20,378
I can have them arrange
a speedy transfer for you.

473
00:34:21,936 --> 00:34:24,230
After you sent me away here,

474
00:34:24,981 --> 00:34:26,857
now you want me to come back?

475
00:34:29,776 --> 00:34:32,320
You can’t just toss me
wherever you want me to be.

476
00:34:32,609 --> 00:34:35,028
Actually, you know what? I can!

477
00:34:36,111 --> 00:34:39,156
If I wanted to, I can drag you
all the way back to Manila.

478
00:34:39,881 --> 00:34:43,843
As long as I’m the one paying
for your education and supporting you,

479
00:34:44,282 --> 00:34:48,077
I can choose where you live
and where you go to school.

480
00:34:48,936 --> 00:34:50,855
Considering everything that’s happened,

481
00:34:51,147 --> 00:34:53,399
it’s probably better
if you stay close to me.

482
00:34:53,742 --> 00:34:56,176
That way, I can watch over you.

483
00:34:56,489 --> 00:34:58,783
I can make sure that this
will never happen again.

484
00:34:59,343 --> 00:35:01,449
You know, Lori, no matter where I put you,

485
00:35:01,965 --> 00:35:04,092
you always end up in trouble.

486
00:35:05,011 --> 00:35:06,471
That’s not true.

487
00:35:07,390 --> 00:35:09,976
Papa, you didn’t even listen to my side.

488
00:35:11,282 --> 00:35:14,160
Papa, I’m not a kid anymore.

489
00:35:14,721 --> 00:35:17,098
I won’t allow you
to control my life again.

490
00:35:17,799 --> 00:35:18,842
You know...

491
00:35:20,438 --> 00:35:22,356
you’re lucky you didn’t get hurt.

492
00:35:23,053 --> 00:35:25,096
Do you even understand that, huh?

493
00:35:27,528 --> 00:35:30,322
You’ve experienced
losing someone you love.

494
00:35:33,784 --> 00:35:34,827
Yes.

495
00:35:35,751 --> 00:35:37,920
I understand that.

496
00:35:39,434 --> 00:35:42,937
But, Papa, I can take care of myself.

497
00:35:45,188 --> 00:35:48,483
The one you saw in the video? Loki?

498
00:35:49,667 --> 00:35:52,420
He’s not violent like that.

499
00:35:52,962 --> 00:35:54,797
He’s not a bad person.

500
00:35:55,186 --> 00:35:58,731
He was just pushed to his limit,
so he snapped.

501
00:35:59,740 --> 00:36:02,118
But I know that doesn’t excuse
what he did.

502
00:36:03,035 --> 00:36:04,704
And now he’s paying for it.

503
00:36:05,413 --> 00:36:07,290
Belive me, I tried to stop him.

504
00:36:09,239 --> 00:36:11,199
Please, Papa.

505
00:36:11,878 --> 00:36:14,213
I don’t want to go back
to St. Bartholomew.

506
00:36:15,015 --> 00:36:16,841
I like it better here at Clark U.

507
00:36:18,259 --> 00:36:22,345
I have friends here,
and I’m needed here, and...

508
00:36:22,346 --> 00:36:24,891
Look, Lori, I know you’re being stubborn.

509
00:36:25,792 --> 00:36:27,085
You know what, you’re right.

510
00:36:28,339 --> 00:36:29,673
You’re of legal age.

511
00:36:30,470 --> 00:36:33,723
You deserve the freedom
to control your own life.

512
00:36:34,955 --> 00:36:36,123
Remember this...

513
00:36:37,317 --> 00:36:40,612
with that freedom comes responsibility.

514
00:36:41,967 --> 00:36:44,553
Okay, let’s do it your way.

515
00:36:45,251 --> 00:36:46,251
For now.

516
00:36:47,023 --> 00:36:48,691
Because if this happens again,

517
00:36:49,284 --> 00:36:52,287
you know what will happen, you understand?

518
00:36:53,502 --> 00:36:54,503
Yes, Papa.

519
00:37:00,176 --> 00:37:01,176
Pa...

520
00:37:04,267 --> 00:37:05,727
It’s been a long day.

521
00:37:06,766 --> 00:37:08,267
I need to get some rest.

522
00:37:09,338 --> 00:37:10,338
Yeah.

523
00:37:18,027 --> 00:37:19,987
By the way, what do you think of Alistair?

524
00:37:21,479 --> 00:37:23,356
Do you think he’s a perfect match for you?

525
00:37:36,354 --> 00:37:37,772
Why is he like that?

526
00:37:38,070 --> 00:37:42,616
We haven’t seen each other in so long,
but it doesn’t seem to matter to him.

527
00:37:45,888 --> 00:37:49,475
I know he cares about me,
but not like a daughter.

528
00:37:53,312 --> 00:37:56,565
More like a piece of property
he checks from time to time.

529
00:37:57,948 --> 00:38:01,535
He even showed up.
He should’ve just texted.

530
00:38:05,160 --> 00:38:06,745
I don't wanna see him anymore.

531
00:38:08,093 --> 00:38:10,012
I wish you were the one here, Mom.

532
00:38:11,358 --> 00:38:12,818
I really miss you.

533
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:37,684
Fresh garlic?

534
00:38:38,774 --> 00:38:40,026
Fried rice?

535
00:38:41,995 --> 00:38:44,039
Is someone cooking in the unit?

536
00:38:45,412 --> 00:38:46,432
But...

537
00:38:47,186 --> 00:38:49,188
Loki doesn't cook.

538
00:38:50,538 --> 00:38:52,164
Maybe it's Tita Martha?

539
00:38:52,952 --> 00:38:56,915
But why would she be cooking
in our unit?

540
00:39:10,052 --> 00:39:11,261
Jamie?

541
00:39:14,003 --> 00:39:15,672
Good morning, Lorelei!

542
00:39:16,272 --> 00:39:18,066
Did you sleep well?

543
00:39:33,038 --> 00:39:34,707
Did you sleep well?

544
00:39:38,350 --> 00:39:39,935
Loki dear!

545
00:39:40,107 --> 00:39:41,651
You two seem to be getting along.

546
00:39:42,236 --> 00:39:45,739
Wow. It's like a newly live-in couple.

547
00:39:49,053 --> 00:39:50,571
Sorry for the interruption.

548
00:39:50,779 --> 00:39:54,575
I would just like to introduce to you
your newest schoolmate.

549
00:39:54,677 --> 00:39:56,846
A transferee student.

550
00:39:58,156 --> 00:40:00,408
Please, come in and introduce yourself.

551
00:40:03,192 --> 00:40:04,192
Al?

552
00:40:04,652 --> 00:40:07,947
Excuse me. Hi. Al, we need to talk.

553
00:40:09,413 --> 00:40:10,581
- Okay.
- Let's go.

554
00:40:11,568 --> 00:40:12,742
Wait, BFF!

555
00:40:12,743 --> 00:40:15,496
I wanted to bring a case to you.

556
00:40:16,802 --> 00:40:18,220
Oh, no.

557
00:40:18,582 --> 00:40:20,458
Ever since Loki has been gone,

558
00:40:20,459 --> 00:40:22,503
we haven't been accepting cases.

559
00:40:24,147 --> 00:40:25,148
Is that so?

560
00:40:25,759 --> 00:40:27,802
But you can tell me.

561
00:40:28,509 --> 00:40:30,969
Welcome. I've been expecting you.

562
00:40:30,970 --> 00:40:34,098
Actually, I'm pleased to finally
meet you face-to-face, Miss Lorelei.

563
00:40:35,348 --> 00:40:37,141
Ever since I watched that video,

564
00:40:37,801 --> 00:40:40,178
I got so much worried about you, Lori.

565
00:40:40,479 --> 00:40:42,480
Loki taught me how to do this

566
00:40:42,481 --> 00:40:44,567
in case something like this happens.

567
00:40:45,592 --> 00:40:47,920
Actually, I feel like
I was really with Loki earlier

568
00:40:47,945 --> 00:40:50,303
with how quick you were able
to decipher that code.

569
00:40:50,808 --> 00:40:52,143
The only difference is

570
00:40:52,483 --> 00:40:54,985
you genuinely care
about the victims and...

571
00:40:55,119 --> 00:40:56,870
you can actually remember their names.

572
00:40:57,184 --> 00:40:58,393
Help!

573
00:41:00,903 --> 00:41:02,529
Help!
